cloud storage:-
 	it is an object storage service used to store unstructured data 
	- files are stored as objects
	- objects are stored inside buckets
	
	Think:

	Bucket = folder
	Object = file (image, video, backup, etc.)
	
	Step-by-step process:
	1. You create a bucket
	2.Upload files → stored as objects
	Each object has:
	 	Data (file)
		Metadata (info like size, type)
	Access using:
		URL
		API
		gcloud

FILESTORE:-
	it is a file storage service(NFS) provides shared file system. multiple vm's apps can access the same files 

			
	
	

	
	
	
	
	
